main event: A witness spotted several bright white lights moving strangely over Palo Alto, California on April 26, 1968.
interesting points: The lights were moving in a strange manner, darting around and then hovering.
The lights suddenly shot off at a high rate of speed.
The witness said the lights were a pure white color and very bright.
The lights were estimated to be at an altitude of around 2,000 feet.
The witness was unable to identify the source of the lights, but was confident they were not conventional aircraft or natural phenomena.
sighted object: Several bright white lights in the sky
